svg.text: Repetition Mark:RMmin = 0.7 RMRMmax = RM + Rt(RM = 2812.5 µs)(Rt = 803.6 µs)
Note:The OnRise mode was too ristrictive withthe leading/repeating marks’ tolerances.With Rt at 11% of RM, Lt could not be higher than 8.33% of LM. Now both Rt and LT are at 28.6%

If both marks have the same tolerance percentage,then: Lt / LM = Rt / RM ⇔ Lt × RM = Rt × LMand because RM+Rt+Lt=LM ⇔ Rt = LM-RM-Lt Substituting into the previous equation we get:Lt × RM = (LM-RM-Lt) × LMand after solving for Lt:Lt=(LM² - LM × RM) / (RM+LM)Knowing that: Rt+Lt=2.25LM=5.0625 and RM=2.8125 we get:Lt = 1.4464 and Rt = 0.8036(Lt is 28.6% of LM and Rt is 28.6% of RM)
